compound operators
  -=
    a -= b AND a = a - b have one difference
    if we are doing lossy conversion, a -= b wont give error, where as a = a - b will give error

    ex
      int a = 2;
      a -= 1.5; // no error
      int a = 2;
      a = a - 1.5; // lossy conversion error
        have to cast
          a = (int) (a - 1.5);


    so -= is actually the short hand with casting
      a -= 1.5;
      in this case is actually the shorthand for
        a = (int) (a - 1.5);


